init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is now very advanced, and the US is just catching up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The rest of the world now wants to help the United States recover, they want to show that they were not wrong in going into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The other countries have something to learn from America, and vice versa.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It is a perfect opportunity for the two to come together and learn from each other.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Many people want to do the right thing but also think of themselves.
